    {
      "id": "trxLzldquCLXO3bdnC4mf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 480.38946533203125,
      "y": 2585.4713745117188,
      "width": 827.699462890625,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b08",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 134865943,
      "version": 403,
      "versionNonce": 377093113,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781490831257,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How nodes communicate?\nGossip protocal\nwhere each server has a list of all other servers, they track the heartbeat\nif no heartbeat received we communicate with other nodes and make that node dead\n\nnodes get information about,\njoins\nleaves\nfailures\nrecoveries\n\nEx : Each node periodically picks a random peer. lets say A -> B\nand exchanges membership information. B merges the information\n\nEpidemic Spread\nWorks like disease propagation. Information spreads exponentially.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How nodes communicate?\nGossip protocal\nwhere each server has a list of all other servers, they track the heartbeat\nif no heartbeat received we communicate with other nodes and make that node dead\n\nnodes get information about,\njoins\nleaves\nfailures\nrecoveries\n\nEx : Each node periodically picks a random peer. lets say A -> B\nand exchanges membership information. B merges the information\n\nEpidemic Spread\nWorks like disease propagation. Information spreads exponentially.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "N-pcfgQRDG7HPio0ne9FM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1457,
      "y": 2598.5,
      "width": 174.69985961914062,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b09",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 90781783,
      "version": 316,
      "versionNonce": 612993591,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781489208939,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Quorum\nw + r > n\nTunable\nStrong consitency\nw = n, r =1\nWeak consistency\nw = 1, r = n\nQuorum\nw + r > n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Quorum\nw + r > n\nTunable\nStrong consitency\nw = n, r =1\nWeak consistency\nw = 1, r = n\nQuorum\nw + r > n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "EiXSyt2NOWxy_CM39C3Ut",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 442.1837792334618,
      "y": 3080.3472444608615,
      "width": 1056.37939453125,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0A",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1489379897,
      "version": 618,
      "versionNonce": 804364503,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781488873614,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\"How do we know whether one write happened after another, or whether two writes happened concurrently?\"\nuse version vectors? read\n\ns1 ( node):  [clientA:1]\ns2 ( node): [clientA:1, clientB:1]\ns3 ( node): [clientC:1]\n\nso we know, [user: no of updates]\ns2 data is latest between s1 and s2.\ns3 and s1 are siblings.\n\nOr \nLast write wins ( LWW)\nAssign a timestamp to updates\n(user:123, value, timestamp)\nProblem : clocks may differ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\"How do we know whether one write happened after another, or whether two writes happened concurrently?\"\nuse version vectors? read\n\ns1 ( node):  [clientA:1]\ns2 ( node): [clientA:1, clientB:1]\ns3 ( node): [clientC:1]\n\nso we know, [user: no of updates]\ns2 data is latest between s1 and s2.\ns3 and s1 are siblings.\n\nOr \nLast write wins ( LWW)\nAssign a timestamp to updates\n(user:123, value, timestamp)\nProblem : clocks may differ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "qdAWz3c43X0GNokC-rCF7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1737.4179972859174,
      "y": 2598.066913555195,
      "width": 591.57958984375,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0B",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 40705975,
      "version": 979,
      "versionNonce": 1783929017,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781489208939,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Sloppy quorum and hinted handoff\nImproves availablity:\nSloppy quorum:\nwe write to any 3 nodes which are not part of initial quorum\nlets say normal quorum\nA B C\nSloppy quorum if B and C are unavilable\nA D E\nProblem : Readers dont know D and E exists and hence\nSloppy quorum weakens consistency.\n\nHinted Handoff:\nhow do we transfer from new temp nodes to actual nodes\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Sloppy quorum and hinted handoff\nImproves availablity:\nSloppy quorum:\nwe write to any 3 nodes which are not part of initial quorum\nlets say normal quorum\nA B C\nSloppy quorum if B and C are unavilable\nA D E\nProblem : Readers dont know D and E exists and hence\nSloppy quorum weakens consistency.\n\nHinted Handoff:\nhow do we transfer from new temp nodes to actual nodes\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "aymX9luErwixcAIZAwZF4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1006.4168031370485,
      "y": 3139.651909369927,
      "width": 592.1596069335938,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0C",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1333795479,
      "version": 538,
      "versionNonce": 358851799,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781488776249,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n\nBloom filter\nIt confidently says that data is not present in the SSTable\nif it says, it is present, it may or may not be present.\nperform & operation and check if it matches\nFiles",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n\nBloom filter\nIt confidently says that data is not present in the SSTable\nif it says, it is present, it may or may not be present.\nperform & operation and check if it matches\nFiles",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Vgngu7GI0d1UvLdFD8col",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2349,
      "y": 2587.5,
      "width": 664.4794921875,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0E",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 956557625,
      "version": 417,
      "versionNonce": 1268040055,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781491050801,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Merkel tree\nA naive anti-entropy repair is expensive. or moving data is expensive\nIdea, \n- Hash data recursively.\n- Leaves represent data ranges.\n- Parent nodes hash children.\n- Root summarizes everything.\nHow to identify k,v pair that has changed",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Merkel tree\nA naive anti-entropy repair is expensive. or moving data is expensive\nIdea, \n- Hash data recursively.\n- Leaves represent data ranges.\n- Parent nodes hash children.\n- Root summarizes everything.\nHow to identify k,v pair that has changed",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
